headline: AT&T COO attacks T-Mobile network claims as misleading
summary: While AT&T (T) missed its third quarter earnings and revenue estimates, it reported adding 405,000 new mobile phone customers alongside an additional 288,000 net fiber subscribers and 270,000 Internet Air subscribers in the latest quarter. AT&T Chief Operating Officer Jeff McElfresh comes on Market Catalysts to talk about the company's latest ad campaign addressing price wars with competitors and T-Mobile's (TMUS) misleading claims over its network coverage size in the US. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts.

headline: AT&T (T) Net Profit Margin Holds at 10.2%, Putting Focus on Value vs. Growth Narratives
summary: AT&T (T) posted revenue growth of just 2% per year, underperforming the broader US market's 10% pace. EPS is forecast to increase at only 0.3% per year, a far cry from the 15.5% annual rise expected for the market, and the company’s most recent net profit margin held steady at 10.2%. Over the past year, annual earnings grew just 1.2%, with that gain pulled down by a $4.9 billion one-off loss. This marks a noticeable slowdown compared to its 5-year average growth of 9%. headline: Nokia posts profit beat as AI, cloud demand boost optical sales
summary: (Reuters) -Nokia reported third-quarter profit which was ahead of market expectations on Thursday, driven by strong optical and cloud demand, including AI-focused data centre sales following its Infinera acquisition.  Comparable operating profit in the quarter through September reached 435 million euros ($507 million).  U.S. tariffs, a market slowdown and a weaker dollar had weighed on Nokia's business this year, prompting it to issue a profit warning in July.
